.TH "gen_pool_alloc_algo_owner" 9 "gen_pool_alloc_algo_owner" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
gen_pool_alloc_algo_owner \- allocate special memory from the pool
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "unsigned long" gen_pool_alloc_algo_owner
.BI "(struct gen_pool *pool "  ","
.BI "size_t size "  ","
.BI "genpool_algo_t algo "  ","
.BI "void *data "  ","
.BI "void **owner "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "pool" 12
pool to allocate from
.IP "size" 12
number of bytes to allocate from the pool
.IP "algo" 12
algorithm passed from caller
.IP "data" 12
data passed to algorithm
.IP "owner" 12
optionally retrieve the chunk owner
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Allocate the requested number of bytes from the specified pool.
Uses the pool allocation function (with first-fit algorithm by default).
Can not be used in NMI handler on architectures without
NMI-safe cmpxchg implementation.
